article.description: Xavier trips Marquette 62-58 behind Abell, Davis
article.headline: Xavier trips Marquette 62-58 behind Abell, Davis
article.linkText: Xavier trips Marquette 62-58 behind Abell, Davis
article.story: CINCINNATI -- Remy Abell scored 15 points, Myles Davis had 14 and freshman Trevon Bluiett hit three clutch free throws in the closing seconds as Xavier edged Marquette 62-58 on Saturday. Marquette, trailing 59-58 inside the final minute, forced a turnover but Luke Fischer missed a contested layup and a tip didn't drop. Xavier pushed the ball upcourt and Bluiett was fouled, making two free throws at 15.7 seconds. Matt Carlino, who had made 6 of 9 3-pointers, couldn't convert on a contested 3 with six seconds left and Bluiett's rebound led to the clinching free throw. Xavier (12-6, 3-3 Big East) improved to 10-0 at home. Carlino finished with 27 for the Golden Eagles (10-7, 2-3). Marquette led 31-22 at the half behind Carlino's 10 points. A barrage of four 3-pointers in four minutes, the last by Abell who had five 3s, put Xavier ahead 47-45 with 7:20 left.
